switch - is used to connect devices within a local network
       - it connect one n/w interface to one another
bridge - connects multiple LAN segments
gateway - connects different networks together, facilitating communication between them
router - is a device that connects different networks together, directing traffic between them and allowing devices to communicate with each other. 
It acts as a traffic controller, determining the most efficient path for data to travel from one network to another.

1 mbps - 10^6 bits/s (1000000 bits/s) 
1 gbps - 10^9 bits/s (1000000000 bits/s)
1 kbps - 1000 bits/s 
